text: A deficient number is when a number is not a perfect number or a abundant number. Also all primes, as well as some prime powers, and any divisors of a perfect or deficient number are deficient. 1 is deficient along with 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 8, 9, 10, 11, 13, 14, 15, 16, 17, 19, 21, 22, 23, etc. ==References== Category:Integer sequences
title: Deficient number
